manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: NATURELO has a unique approach to formulating our supplements — we always use the cleanest most bioavailable ingredients whenever possible so that you can get the most benefit from each supplement. We seek out plant-based nutrients which means sourcing vitamin E from sunflowers (instead of synthetics), Vitamin D from lichen (instead of animal based lanolin which comes from sheep grease!) and Calcium from marine algae (instead of cheaper calcium carbonate which is actually made from rocks!) If that isn’t enough, we also boost our supplements with proprietary blends of organic fruits, vegetables and botanicals for an extra source of real whole food nutrition. Like organic broccoli, carrots, blueberries, kale, spinach, heart healthy turmeric, immune boosting mushrooms… we could go on and on and on… Naturelo... from Nature with Love

Plant-Based Nutrition Real food ingredients grown in sunshine, water, and soil. Keepin’ it Clean Non-GMO with no artificial preservatives or additives. Whole Body Health Supplements that support energy, health, and well-being. 3rd Party Verified Made in a GMP-audited facility and lab tested for purity.

Energy & Focus Iron helps red blood cells transport oxygen to your cells to help keep you energized and refreshed.* Women’s Health Iron is essential for building healthy blood, which is especially important for menstruating or pregnant women.* Physical Performance Iron supports physical work capacity & endurance by keeping muscles oxygenated and supporting energy.*

You May Be at Risk of Low Iron If: You Menstruate Blood loss during menstruation can deplete iron stores, making women more vulnerable to iron depletion.* You’re Vegetarian or Vegan The iron found in vegetarian foods is more difficult for the body to absorb than the iron found in animal products.* You Work Out a Lot Intense exercise increases iron demands, while more iron is also lost through sweat, increasing the risk of iron depletion.* You Have a Gut Condition Intestinal disorders such as celiac disease or Inflammatory Bowel Disease can impair iron absorption in the gut.*

reviews.reviewText: Gentle on the stomach! No nausea or constipation from these. They also don't smell metallic-y or have that metallic aftertaste. They smell like vegetables/fruit and no aftertaste at all. The capsules aren't too big and are easy to swallow. I take mine in the evening with my dinner (around 6pm) and haven't had any issues with stomach upset at all. I've noticed my bruising is significantly less and my energy levels do seem to be improving. I can't speak on the actual levels in the blood as I haven't been re-tested but based on how I'm feeling, I'd say these work well! I am definitely going to continue to purchase this product.
